          'Output filter design: an inductor in series with the output passes 60Hz but blocks high-frequency switching content. A capacitor in parallel with the load completes the filter. Together (L-C filter), they attenuate the switching frequency ripple while passing the 60Hz sine wave cleanly. The cutoff frequency of the filter must be well below the switching frequency but well above 60Hz.',
          'Load response: when the load changes suddenly (e.g., a large motor starts), the inverter controller must respond rapidly to maintain stable voltage. Slow response causes voltage sags during load steps. Fast-switching IGBTs combined with closed-loop voltage control ensure the inverter output stays within regulation limits even during large transients.',
