          'Vented (flooded) lead-acid: liquid sulfuric acid electrolyte, requires periodic water addition (maintenance), vents hydrogen gas during charging. Used in large stationary applications (telecommunications, utilities) where maintenance access is available. Must be installed in ventilated battery rooms with appropriate spill containment.',
          'Battery ratings: capacity in ampere-hours (Ah) at a specified discharge rate. A 100Ah battery rated at 8-hour rate (C/8) means 12.5A for 8 hours. At higher discharge rates (C/4, C/1), actual usable capacity decreases (Peukert effect). Temperature also affects capacity — capacity drops significantly below 20°C.',
